Introduction

·         This document, our Privacy Policy, governs how EasyEncrypt (“we”, “us”, “EasyEncrypt”) handles our users’ (“you,” “your,” etc.) data on the EasyEncrypt desktop app itself (the “EasyEncrypt App” or “EasyEncrypt”). Our Privacy Policy is incorporated into and is subject to the EasyEncrypt Terms of Service, so please read both documents carefully. Your use of the Services indicates your consent to this Privacy Policy and our Terms of Service. If you do not want to be bound by these agreements, you may not use our Services. We work very hard to preserve your privacy and security, and we do our best to be as transparent as possible in explaining how we use your data in providing our Services.

EasyEncrypt Desktop App
Our Privacy Practices in Brief:

EasyEncrypt provides messages encoding offline to users around the world. This is for a desktop application that encodes a message offline, can be used to send secure encoded message. This application uses AES and DES algorithms based on user choice to encrypt and decrypt text.

We can’t see information you send through the EasyEncrypt App. Your information is always disguised through AES and DES algorithms based on user choice to encrypt and decrypt text. Because of this we don’t know — and can’t reveal to others — anything about you or how you use the EasyEncrypt App.
When you send end-to-end encrypted messages using EasyEncrypt, it is important to note that if you do not trust the person you’re talking to, do not open messages coming from them or send them messages you do not want to be saved.
You own your data. We do not share or sell any data about our users. Period.
The types of personal information we collect and how we collect it

·         We are committed to limiting our collection of your information to what is necessary to provide you with our Services.

·         We operate and provide our Services, including providing customer support, and improving, fixing, and customizing our Services. We understand how people use our Services, and analyze and use the information we have to evaluate and improve our Services, research, develop, and test new services and features, and conduct troubleshooting activities.

What We Don’t Collect

·         Equally important to us is the information we don’t collect. We will NEVER collect any location information or have access to the contents of the communications you send using the EasyEncrypt App.

What Information Does EasyEncrypt  Share with Third Parties?

·         We do not share any user information we have with third parties. We may also share or disclose your information with your consent, for example if you use a third party application to access your account.

 

Security 

 In accordance with our requirements, we will adopt appropriate security procedures to help prevent unauthorised access to your information. We shall not be liable for any attempt to hack or crack or otherwise gain access to any part of this application including any of your information.

 

Business Transfers

If  EasyEncrypt or substantially all of its assets, were acquired or in the unlikely event  that EasyEncrypt goes out of business or enters bankruptcy – user information would be one of the assets that would be transferred or acquired by a third party. You acknowledge that such transfers may occur, and that any acquirer of EasyEncrypt may continue to use your personal information as set forth in this policy.

 

Policy changes

 By using this website you agree to the terms of this privacy policy and our terms of use. We may amend this privacy policy and the terms of use from time to time. If we do so, we will post an updated version on this website. You will be bound by the new terms upon your continued use of this website.

 

